{"build_type":"library","description":"Host compatibility module memory primitive: the single place that asks the host for a raw memory chunk. Maps len bytes of anonymous private memory and returns the base address. On Linux this is the mmap syscall; on bare metal it would take physical pages from the hardware. The native bump allocator calls this once per chunk and then manages the arena itself, so memory management never proxies per allocation. Eventually the only memory sys site in the universe. When the pool is armed (g_kernel_pool_end != 0) it routes through grant-pool-chunk-parking-until-available (design section 5 soft degradation: self-starve fail-hard else park-on-exhaustion), which never returns zero.","module_name":"allocate-system-memory-chunk-region","package_name":"allocate-system-memory-chunk-region","function_definitions":{"allocate-system-memory-chunk-region":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"len","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"global_read","dest":"poolend","name":"g_kernel_pool_end"},{"instruction_type":"conditional_branch","condition_type":"numeric_compare","operator":"!=","lhs":{"value":"poolend"},"rhs":{"value":"zero"},"branch_on_success":[{"instruction_type":"function_invocation","invocation_name":"grant-pool-chunk-parking-until-available","invocation_arguments":[{"kind":"var","value":"len"}],"result_assignment_variable":"g","result_type":"i64"},{"instruction_type":"return_statement","return_payload":{"value":"g"}}],"branch_on_failure":[]},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"prot","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":3},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"flags","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":16418},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"nfd","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":-1},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"__t0","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"__t0","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"__t0","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"invoke_kernel_syscall","syscall_number":"9","arg1":"zero","arg2":"len","arg3":"prot","arg4":"flags","arg5":"nfd","arg6":"zero","result_variable":"base"},{"instruction_type":"return_statement","return_payload":{"value":"base"}}]}}}